{
  "texts": [
    "The DLA collects features from CNN layers to determine the shared features, i.e.",
    "it aggregates features at each layer relating to a verified joint and tries to classify what it is (knee, elbow, etc.",
    ").For optimization, the model is updated with adaptive strategies relating to the confidence weight of each pixel and their corresponding weighted fusion sumbased on the joint classification.",
    "This methods shows significant improvement in joint and posture detection compared to other state-of-the-art methods (Wang and Li 2013; Pishchulin et al. 2013; Hossain and Little 2018; Pavllo et al. 2019).",
    "In contrast, Bridgeman et al. (2019) looks at tracking and analysing multiple targets simultaneously."
  ]
}